content:
Starting in Spring ’22, Salesforce began enabling Lightning Web Security (LWS) in some customer orgs. To minimize disruption for customers with highly customized environments, we’re postponing automatic enablement until further notice. If LWS isn’t enabled yet in your org, we encourage you to enable it in a sandbox environment to test your components running in LWS.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in all editions.
